reviews.review_text: One of the few For the Ages shows of post 1983 era The Rhythm Devils section maybe the finest i ever heard- so so so trippy, ahhhhhhhhh!!!

An Acid Test Opening! What a HOOT to hear the boys dorking around so hilariously at the start. "Frozen Logger" is always a welcome bit of nuttery. Really got the smiles and energy flowing through the joint. Just a goofy-assed show, with plenty of "old" songs and odd songs throughout. 
I used this for the 9-7 #DeadOnThisDate offering on twitter.
Thank you, Mr. Seamons.
5-stars and a big grin for this fine piece of work! Hot on the Rocks!
